.Dd March 3, 2003
.Dt WCTOB 3
.Os
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh NAME
.Nm wctob
.Nd convert a wide character to a single byte character
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libc
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In wchar.h
.Ft int
.Fn wctob "wint_t wc"
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn wctob
function converts a wide character
.Fa wc
to a corresponding single byte character in the initial shift state of
the current locale.
.Pp
The behaviour of
.Fn wctob
is affected by the
.Dv LC_CTYPE
category of the current locale.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh RETURN VALUES
The
.Fn wctob
function returns:
.Bl -tag -width 012345678901
.It Dv EOF
If
.Fa wc
is
.Dv WEOF
or if
.Fa wc
does not correspond to a valid single byte character representation.
.It (otherwise)
A single byte character corresponding to
.Fa wc .
.El
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh ERRORS
No errors are defined.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr btowc 3 ,
.Xr setlocale 3 ,
.Xr wcrtomb 3
.\" ----------------------------------------------------------------------
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Fn wctob
function conforms to
.St -isoC-amd1 .
